ASSIGNMENT #1 (Group):  Communication Covenant due January 12
	 
	A Communication Covenant is an agreement every member of a team makes about communicating: 
	·  	promising to communicate regularly (even when the news is bad),
	·  	promising to answer your email how many times a day,
	·  	agreeing that you will be using Google Docs for file management,
	·  	specifying when and where your meetings are (1-2 times a week),
	·  	promising to notify team mates if you can’t make a meeting,
	·  	agreeing to reasonable punishments if a team mate is late or misses without notifying everyone,
	·  	promising to volunteer to do things and to do them well and on time. 
	 
	Include a table of preferred email addresses and cell phone numbers.  Title the file TEAMNAMEContacts
	 
	Put this file in the Google Docs folder your team is sharing with us.

6.1. Modes of Communication
	6.1.1. Norms Regarding Modes of Communication:
In Case of Late or Lack of Response

Meetings should start within the first 5 minutes of the designated meeting time. In the instances where a document/deliverable is to be worked on, an agenda will be prepared beforehand to follow. Team members should come prepared with the necessary documents and know the issues that need to be worked.

In Case of Tardiness or Absence
If a team member is late to a meeting, regardless the amount of time, the team will take 5-10 minutes to recap on the topics that had been discussed in their absence. In all cases of tardiness or absence, the offending member should contact the rest of the team, notifying them of the situation prior to the beginning of the meeting.
In the event that a team member is late or absent from a meeting, the meeting will be conducted regardless of their presence. It will be that team member’s responsibility to learn what they missed, and make up any work that may be expected of them.
6.2.1.4.1. In Case of Tardiness or Absence Without Prior Notification:
If a team member is more than 10 minutes late, that member must supply snacks/drinks for the next meeting.
If a team member is more than 30 minutes late, they must schedule and organize the next meeting as well as supply it with snacks/drinks.
If a team member is more than 1 hour late, they must spear head the next document/deliverable(s) (as decided reasonable by the rest of the team), schedule and organize the next team meeting as well as supply snacks/drinks to that meeting.
			6.2.1.4.2. Regarding Corrective Measure
If a team member is late or absent but has appropriately informed the group ahead of time, no extreme punitive measures will be taken. If that team member’s absences and/or tardiness becomes excessive, then their place on the team will be assessed by the others, and their removal may be considered. Corrective measures for other instances are listed above, in section 2.1.4.1.
